results.name: Number of times the digit 9 appears in the decimal expansion of n^3.
comment: The cubes corresponding to the first occurrence of 1, 2, 3, ... are listed in A036535, i.e., A036535(n)^(1/3) = A048374(n) is the index of the first occurrence of n.
link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
xref: Analog for squares: A086017 (digit 9) and A086008 - A086016 for digits 0 - 8.
